Carmel Upsidedown French Toast 
Rich, moist, and gooey, this overnight Soufflé French toast recipe will have you swooooooning!

Ingredients:
1/2 cup melted butter (1 stick)
1 cup brown sugar
1 loaf brioche 
4 eggs
1 1/2 cup milk
1 teaspoon vanilla
Cinnamon 
Powdered sugar for sprinkling

Combine the butter and brown sugar in a small sauce pan and cook till well combined and bubbling. Pour onto a prepared baking pan. Prepare your batter and dip your brioche bread in to soak well and then add on top of the carmel. Pour remaining batter on top. Cover and refrigerate overnight, bake at 350°F for 30 minutes covered, then 15 minutes uncovered. Cut each piece and plate upside down (carmel side up). Dust with powdered sugar and drizzle with maple syrup if desired.

For variations, try putting sweet cream cheese (or any other filling option) in between the brioche layers 🤤🤤

Chimichurri on Garlic Chili Skirt Steak

Steak Marinade:
1 lb skirt steak
½ C olive oil
¼ C Worcestershire sauce
¼ C soy sauce 
2 TBS apple cider vinegar 
1 tsp garlic powder
1 tsp cumin
1 tsp paprika
1 tsp salt
1/2 tsp black pepper

Chimichurri Sauce:
1 C flat-leaf parsley
¼ C cilantro
¼ C oregano
⅓ C red onion, roughly chopped
3 cloves garlic
½ tsp red pepper flakes
½ C extra-virgin olive oil
¼ C apple cider vinegar
3 TBS  lemon juice
1 tsp salt 

Combine marinade ingredients in a ziplock bag and add skirt steak. Seal up bag and allow to marinate for a minimum of 2 hours - the longer the better. 

Place all chimichurri ingredients in a food processor and blend until fine and combined, or if you choose to hand chop, finely chop your herbs and onion, grate your garlic, and add remaining ingredients to a bowl and combine.

Once steak is done marinating, cook using your preferred method (stove top, grill, etc). Once removed from heat, lightly salt, then allow to rest covered for at least 10 minutes. Once ready, slice steak and plate atop preferred carb, then top with chimichurri and enjoy! 🤤

Brown Butter Salted Chocolate Chip Cookies

¾ C butter, browned
1 C brown sugar
¼ C white sugar
1 whole egg
1 egg yolk
1 Tbs vanilla
1¾ C flour
¾ tsp baking soda
Pinch of salt
2 C Chocolate chips 

Brown the butter and then add in sugars and combine well. Add eggs and vanilla and combine well again. Then add flour, baking soda, and salt and combine till the flour is barely visible. Then fold in chocolate chips. Scoop into balls and place on a cookie sheet. Chill for at least 30 minutes then bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes. Cookies should look underdone when you pull them out but will harden a little once they cool ❤️

Gochujang Broccolini with Spicy Peanut Sauce

Marinade:
1 lb broccolini 
2 Tbs gochujang sauce (I used Trader Joes)
2 Tbs sesame oil
2 Tbs rice vinegar 
2 Tbs sesame seeds

Sauce Ingredients:
3 Tbs peanut butter
3 Tbs soy sauce
1 Tbs Sambal
2 Tbs honey
1 Tbs sesame oil
1 Tbs rice vinegar 
2 cloves garlic, grated

Garnish:
Fresh lime juice 
Peanuts, chopped
Cilantro, chopped
Scallions/green onion, sliced 

Whisk together the broccolini marinade ingredients and toss in the broccolini. Place on a baking sheet and roast at 400°F for about 20-30 minutes (flip at the last 10 minutes). My preference is to roast until the tips are lightly browned ans crispy.
Meanwhile combine the sauce ingredients well. 
For plating, spoon sauce to the bottom of your dish, place roasted broccolini on top, drizzle some more peanut sauce on top, then garnish with a squeeze of lime, chopped peanuts, chopped cilantro and sliced scallions/green onion. Enjoy!

Glazed Mixed Berry Sweet Focaccia 

5.25 C flour
1 packet yeast
2.5 C water
1 Tbs olive oil
1 Tbs salt

Combine dough ingredients well. Then put dough in an oiled, clean bowl and allow to rise for 3 hours. Every hour, come back and knock it down. Transfer the dough to a prepared baking sheet and allow to rise one last time for one hour. Meanwhile, make the macerated berries:
½ C strawberries, diced
½ C raspberries, halved
½ C blueberries, halved
Zest from one orange
4 tsp sugar
½ tsp vanilla

Spoon your macerated berries on top of your poofy focaccia dough and then massage and dimple it - the juicier, the better. Then sprinkle the top of your dough lightly with some white sugar.
Bake at 425° for 20-25 minutes. Meanwhile combine 1 C powdered sugar and 1.5 Tbs milk to make the glaze.
Once the focaccia is done baking, pull it out of the oven and allow to cool, then pour the glaze on top evenly and enjoy the same day! Its so good!

Garlic Herb Potato Salad

3 C chopped small potato of choice
⅓ C fresh dill, chopped
¼ C fresh parsley, chopped
1 Tbs fresh thyme
2 Tbs lemon juice
2 Tbs pickled onions (or fresh red)
3 Tbs capers, chopped
½ C feta
Salt and pepper to taste

Dressing:
½ C mayo
¼ C sour cream
1½ Tbs lemon juice
2 Tbs olive oil
1 lemon zest
3 cloves garlic
Salt and pepper to taste

Quarter and boil potatoes in salted water. Meanwhile combine dressing ingredients and herbs in a large servinf bowl. Once potatoes are fork tender, drain and add to the bowl of dressing. Toss and enjoy warm or refrigerate and serve cold - either way its delicious!

Peanut Butter and Jelly Cookies

10 Tbs butter 
½ C white sugar
½ C brown sugar
1.5 tsp vanilla 
1 large egg
⅓ C peanut butter
1¼ C flour 
½ tsp baking soda 
½ tsp salt
¼ C preserves

Preheat oven to 350°F
Brown the butter in a saucepan, then add to a standmixer (or hand mix if you prefer). Allow to cool for 10 minutes. Add sugars and vanilla to butter and mix till well combined and cooled. Add in egg, then add peanut butter. Lastly, add in the dry ingredients (flour, salt, baking soda) and mix until combined well. Scoop dough with a cookie scoop to get them uniform in size. Form the dough into a well and fill with preserves, and close up the dough ball. Press into baking sheet and bake on a parchment lined cookie sheet for 12-14 minutes. Let cool for 10 minutes before moving. Then enjoy!

Balsamic Roasted Tomato Marinara 

2 lbs ripe tomatoes 
1 onion, chopped
2 Tbs olive oil
4 cloves garlic
⅛ C balsamic vinegar 
1 tsp salt
½ tsp pepper
2 Tbs italian seasoning
1 tsp sugar
½ tsp red pepper flake
1 Boursin Garlic & Herb cheese

Coarsely chop all produce and add to a baking sheet. Top with all seasoning and combine well, while separating onions. 
Bake at 450° for 30-40 minutes. 
Pour all contents into a blender with boursin cheese and blend until smooth. Make sure to check your seasonings to see if you need more salt. Add to any cooked pasta, top with Parmesan.

Gooey Snickerdoodle Blondies

2⅓ C flour 
1.5 tsp baking powder
½ tsp salt
¾ C butter
¾ C white sugar
¾ C brown sugar
2 eggs
2 tsp vanilla 
1 C marshmallows 

Filling:
¼ C sugar
1 Tbs cinnamon

Preheat your oven to 350°F and line a 11x7 baking pan with parchment paper. Beat together butter and sugar till creamy, then mix in eggs and vanilla. Lastly, add the dry ingredient: flour, baking soda, salt and combine well. 
Spoon half the batter into the baking pan and spread out evenly. Then sprinkle on the filling mixture (save 1 Tbs of filling for later), then add the marshmallows. Lastly, spoon on the last half of the batter on top and using your fingers, spread to cover the marshmallows the best you can. Top with the remaining tablespoon of cinnamon sugar and then bake for 30-35 minutes or until a toothpick comes or clean. Cool completely before cutting ❤️

Thai Spring Rolls with Peanut Sauce

Sauce: 
⅓ C fish sauce
1 can sugar free ginger ale
2 Tbs Sriacha (or sambal) - to taste
10 cloves garlic, minced
1 C peanuts, toasted and smashed

Rolls:
1 head romaine, cleaned and de-ribbed
3 carrots, peeled
1 cucumbers, peeled
6 oz bean sprouts
1 C fresh mint 
1 C fresh basil
1 lb shrimp, de-vained, boiled, & peeled

Garlic oil: 
¼ C olive oil 
5 garlic minced

Combine all sauce ingredients in a bowl.
Lightly fry the garlic in oil to make the garlic oil. 
Lightly wet rice paper in warm water. Lay flat and layer on veggies, herbs, and shrimp, then roll up. Roll closed spring roll in the garlic oil. Serve with sauce, and eat immediately ❤️

Before anyone eats me alive, i know ginger ale isn’t traditional but she says its a delish shortcut. Also, she puts rice noodles in hers, but I choose to leave them out ❤️

Creamy Chicken and Calabrian Chili Pasta

8 oz chicken sausage
1 shallot, sliced 
3 cloves garlic, minced
3 Tbs tomato paste
4 Tbs white or rice wine vinegar
1 tsp calabrian chilies (or more to taste)
8 oz dry pasta
½ tsp garlic powder 
3 oz mascarpone (or cream)
1 C frozen peas
½ C fresh parm

Garnish:
Fresh basil
Olive oil
Parmesan 

Bring a pot of salted water to a boil. In a large or deep fry pan, cook sausage, breaking it up. Add shallots, garlic and salt and toss to combine. Then add tomato paste, vinegar, garlic powder, and calabrian chilies. Once combined well, add dry pasta to the sauce with two ladels of salted water. Allow water to cook down, stiring the pasta. If pan gets too dry and pasta isnt cooked to proper done-ness, add another ladle. Continue adding ladles and cooking off the salted water till pasta is cooked. Add mascarpone, peas, and fresh parm. Plate the pasta and top with basil, olive oil, and more fresh parm - enjoy!
Note: all chicken sausage is made with different herbs and seasoning, so make sure you taste along the way to make sure your flavors are to your liking ❤️

Butter Pecan Cookies

2.5 C flour
1 Tbs cornstarch 
½ tsp salt
½ tsp cinnamon 
1 tsp baking soda
1C butter, browned
1C brown sugar
½C white sugar
1 Tbs vanilla 
2 eggs + 1 egg yolk

1C pecans, chopped
3 Tbs butter

Brown up butter and add to a mixing bowl with both sugars and vanilla and mix until well combined and cooled. Beat in eggs. Add all dry ingredients in and fold to combine. 
Combine pecans and butter on the stove to toast up. Once cooled, add to the batter and fold in.
Scoop into about 3Tbs sized balled and place on a parchment lined baking sheet. Top with a whole pecan and press in. Bake at 375°F for 10 minutes. As soon as you pull out the cookies, top with a small pinch of granulated sugar. Enjoy!

Moroccan Spiced Whole Cauliflower 

1 head cauliflower 
1 tsp coriander 
½ tsp cumin
1 tsp paprika 
½ tsp turmeric 
½ tsp allspice 
1 tsp garlic powder 
1 tsp dried thyme
¼ C olive oil
Salt and pepper to taste

Sauces:
1 tsp harissa paste
2 Tbs olive oil

2 Tbs Tahini
1 Tbs lemon juice
2 Tbs yogurt
1 clove garlic, grated
Salt to taste

Garnish:
1 Tbs fresh mint, chopped
¼ C toasted pine nuts
3 dates, chopped

Preheat oven to 450°. Clean cauliflower and steam for 25 minutes. Toast seasonings in a pan then add olive oil and combine into a paste. Transfer cauliflower into an oven safe dish and cover in the spice paste and roast in the oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Then broil for 2 to 5 minutes or until the top is crispy. Combine the harissa and olive oil in a small bowl. In a separate bowl, combine tahini, lemon juice, garlic, and salt. Once the cauliflower is cooked, remove from the oven and top with the tahini sauce, harissa oil, pinenuts, mint, and dates.

Strawberry Shortbread Streusel Bars

Base: Combine ¾C butter with ⅓C sugar, then add 1½C flour, 1 Tbs cornstarch, ¼ tsp salt, and ½ tsp vanilla. Press the dough firmly into a parchment paper lined 8x8 pan and bake at 300°F for 20 minutes.
Once done, remove from the oven and turn the oven up to 350°.
Filling: Combine 2 cups diced strawberries, 1 Tbs sugar, and 2 tsp cornstarch. Spoon on top of baked shortbread crust (leave out the juice).
Streusel Topping: combine ¾C flour, ⅓C shaved coconut, ⅓C chopped pecans, ⅓C brown sugar, 2 Tbs white sugar, ½ tsp cinnamon, ¼ tsp salt. Once combined add ¼C melted butter and combine. Sprinkle on top of strawberry mixture. Bake at 350°F for 30-35 minutes or until golden brown. Cool fully before cutting.

Creamy Pea and Pancetta Orzo

4oz pancetta
1 leek whites, sliced
3 garlic, minced
1 C cherry tomatoes, halved
1 C peas
1 C orzo
1 Tbs Better Than Boullion 
2oz goat cheese
1 Tbs lemon juice
2 Tbs pinenuts, toasted
1 tsp salt 
1 tsp italian seasonjng
Red pepper flakes to taste
Fresh parsley, chopped

Crisp up pancetta in a large frying pan. Add in sliced leeks and minced garlic and sauté till lightly golden. Add in halved cherry tomatoes and peas. Combine well, then mix in orzo, 2 C water, Better Than Bullion, and salt and stir till the Bullion disintegrates. Add in the goat cheese, italian seasoning, ½ tsp pepper. Cover and cook for 20 minutes or until water is fully absorbed. Uncover, taste for seasonings and adjust accordingly, then mix in lemon juice. Plate and garnish with toasted pinenuts, and fresh chopped parsley.

Baba Ganoush - The recipe passed down for generations in my family ❤️

2 eggplant, roasted and peeled
2 heaping TBS tahini 
1 clove garlic, grated
¼ C lemon juice
1.5 tsp salt

Char your eggplant over an open fire or on a grill, then place in a bowl and cover. Once theyve cooled, uncover and scrape the skins off. Place in a clean bowl with tahini, garlic, lemon juice, and salt and combine well while breaking up the eggplant. Plate, then garnish with olive oil, fresh chopped parsley, pomegranate seeds, and paprika - enjoy! ❤️

Apple Pie with Oat Pecan Crumble

Pie Crust (homemade or store bought):
1¼ C flour
½ C cold butter, cubed
½ C ice cold water (or less)
1 Tbs sugar
½ tsp salt
Combine flour, salt, sugar. Add cubed butter to the dry mixture and using your hands, massage the butter into the flour till it resembles sand. Slowly begin to add in your ice water till the dough is fully formed.
If your dough feels a little wet, roll it around in flour before rolling it flat into the crust. Using a rolling pin, roll it to a 12” round (this will fit a 9” pan). Place it into the pie pan and cut off any overflow edges.
Filling:
2.5 lbs apples (~6), cored and sliced
8 Tbs butter
3 Tbs flour
1 tsp cinnamon
¼ C water
1 C sugar
Pinch of nutmeg
¼ tsp salt
In a deep pot, melt the butter then whisk in the flour. Once golden, add in the remaining ingredients and combine till a caramel has formed. Add in apples and mix well to coat the apples before turning the fire off. Pour into the pie pan with all the drippings. Give the pie pan a shake to help the apple settle.
Crumble:
Combine 1 C flour, ½ C chopped pecans, ½ C whole oats, ½ C brown sugar, ½ C white sugar, ½ tsp cinnamon. Once well combined, add butter and using your fingers or a fork, mash together, creating a crumble texture. Sprinkle on top of apples and spread out. Bake at 375°F for 50-60minutes. Cool for at least 1 hour before cutting.

Oldie but Goodie: Fall Harvest Salad with Crispy Quinoa 

Ingredients:
Romaine lettuce
Cucumber
Red onion
Pecans
Cranberries
Feta
Roasted sweet potatoes
Crispy quinoa 
Apple cider vinaigrette

Peel then chop up sweet potatoes into one inch cubes and toss with salt, pepper, and everything but the elote seasoning (if you dont have it, its mainly chili powder and a touch of cumin). Roast at 400° for 30-40 minutes or until soft in the center and slightly browned on the outside.

For the crispy quinoa, cook up ½ C quinoa with 1 C water and 1 tsp salt. Once cooked, pour out onto a parchment paper lined baking sheet and add 1 tsp olive oil, and Garlic Citrus seasoning from Trader Joes (for something similar, try Tajin, or lemon pepper seasoning with garlic powder). Toss and then roast at 400° for 25-30 minutes.

Lastly, for the dressing, combine:
¼ C Apple Cider Vinegar
2 Tbs Dijon mustard
1.5 TBS lemon juice
1 Tbs honey
1 clove garlic, grated
½ tsp salt
¼ tsp black pepper
½ C extra-virgin olive oil

Butternut Squash Soup with Parmesan Crusted Croutons 

Ingredients:
1 whole head garlic, roasted
1 medium sized butternut squash, peeled and cut into 1 inch cubes
1 sweet onion, roughly chopped
2 tsp dried thyme
1 tsp chili powder 
1 tsp salt
½ tsp pepper

Chop off the root of the garlic, and place garlic in foil with a healthy drizzle of olive oil, a pinch of salt and pepper, and roast at 425° for 40-45 minutes. Meanwhile, toss remaining ingredients and roast at 425° for 35 minutes (both items can share the oven).
While the vegetables roast, make your Parmesan crusted croutons by buttering some sliced bread, and placing on a hot pan. Grate Parmesan on top then flip and repeat on the other side till both sides are crispy and golden - it should only take minutes per side. 
Once the garlic and squash have finished roasting, add both to a pot with 4 C vegetable stock (or 4 C water with a heaping tablespoon of Better Than Bouillon). Bring up to a simmer and then using an immersion blender (or regular blender), blend till smooth and creamy. Taste and adjust seasonings to taste (I like to add extra black pepper here to add a little heat).
To plate, pour soup into a bowl, swirl on cream (or you can use plain yogurt thinned out with a little water), Parmesan crusted croutons, fresh thyme, and sumac. Enjoy!

Aish El Saraya Arabic Dessert

3 Tbs sugar
1½ C milk
½ C cream
1 tsp Orange Blossom Water

Add sugar to a large pot and cook until it liquifies and becomes golden. Then add hot water and stir in your semolina/farina and stir until a dough forms - add more hot water if it thickens up too quickly. Scoop the dough into a 9x13 tray and smooth out then allow to cool fully. Meanwhile, mix the custard ingredients and add to the top of the cooled dough and spread out evenly. Teta’s Koosa Mahshi

30 zucchini 
2 C rice 
1 lbs ground lamb/beef
½ tsp Cardamom 
1 tsp Turmeric
2 tsp Salt
1 tsp black Pepper
1 tsp allspice 
½ tsp Cumin
¼ C olive oil

1 large can San Marzano Tomatoes, puréed 
2 C Greek yogurt 
1 Tbs corn starch

Place your rice in a bowl if water and allow to soak while you prepare the zucchini.
Wash and dry the zucchinis, cut off the stalks and slice off the dried tips at the opposite end without removing too much flesh.
Carefully hollow out the zucchini. Start from the stalk end by inserting your corer about 3/4 of the way into the zucchini, making sure not to poke the bottoms. Twist the corer and pull out the zucchini flesh. Do this a few times, until you have a generous cavity. Place in a bowl of salted water as you core the rest of your zucchinis.
Combine drained rice, meat, spices, and olive oil and begin stuffing your hollowed out zucchini about ¾ of the way full. Add to a pressure cooker.
In a separate pot, combine the full fat greek yogurt and the cornstarch, then add the puréed tomatoes, and bring to a boil. Once boiling, pour on top of the zucchini and bring up to a boil again. Cover the pressure cooker and cook 5 minutes on high, 5 minutes on low, then uncover and cook until the zucchini is tender, the rice is soft, and the sauce is to your preferred consistency. If you don’t have a pressure cooker, cover your pot and simmer for 45 minutes. Then enjoy!!

Cheese Stuffed Olive Focaccia 

Combine:
5.25 C all purpose flour
1 packet yeast
2.5C water 
1 Tbs salt
1 Tbs Olive Oil

Pour 3TBS olive oil in a clean bowl, add your dough, and let rise 1 hour, knock down and then pour out into an oiled cookie sheet and let rise again for another hour, then knock it down one more time and sprinkle the cheese all over the top. Bring in the edges to cover the cheese well, then fold and let rise on last time. In the meantime grind together 1/2 C sliced olives, 1 Tbs olive brine, 2 cloves garlic, and the zest from one lemon. Scoop the olive mixture evenly on top the dough and begin to dimple the dough allowing little bubbles to come through (avoid the big bubbles for this one), making sure you don’t puncture through to the cheese. Bake in a 425°F oven for 20-25 minutes or until the top is crusty and golden brown.
